{
  "texts": [
    "This is important, not only to separate AI-and human-generated content, but to broadcast safety from the unpredictable outputs of AI (not by AI, 2023).",
    "The use of AI has shifted dramatically considering recent developments, most notably, the availability of large-scale generative AI to the public.",
    "This shift has transformed the most common domain expertise of AI from the theoretical-technical context, into the practical, or \"layman\", context, where non-AI experts derive insight from generative AI constructs, e.g., ChatGPT, by simply prompting in their natural language.",
    "This shift has implications for individual thought processing, digital media, intellectual property laws, academia, and job skills.",
    "In some occupation areas, indeed, humans may be replaced, or have their work significantly augmented, by the new wave of Large Language Models."
  ]
}